    <text id="F8034T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Wood requests to use Cameron's name for the presidential nomination of the
                    Republican party.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
               

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1859-12-31"><abbr expan="December">Dec</abbr> 31th/<abbr
                                expan="1859">59</abbr></date>
                        <name type="place">Chambersburg</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="General">Gen.</abbr> Cameron,<lb/>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have been requested to ask you for the use of your name by many of your
                    political friends along with the friends of the new proprietors and Editors of
                    the Chambersburg times, a newspaper that we have just started in this place, to
                    go to the top of its Columns as the candidate for the presidency in 1860--</p>
                <p>I send you a copy of the paper and hope that this appeal may not be in vain, you
                    will please address me as Soon as convenient on the subjects.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Truly</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">Lafayette Wood</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient">To<lb/><abbr expan="Honorable">Hon.</abbr>
                            <abbr expan="Simon">S.</abbr> Cameron</name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
